1
00:00:00,733 --> 00:00:02,167
If he worked with Mr. Fernandez,

2
00:00:02,167 --> 00:00:04,633
<i>he might already know
the ins and outs of the hotel.</i>

3
00:00:04,633 --> 00:00:06,100
<i> If Sandro is still alive,</i>

4
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:07,667
<i> that means he's the one
who killed Dad.</i>

5
00:00:07,667 --> 00:00:09,500
<i>Andy and Sandro could be
working together.</i>

6
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,033
<i> My gut's telling me it's him!</i>

7
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:13,433
<i>They think
they can outsmart me.</i>

8
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:15,400
<i>I'll be keeping an eye
on all of you.</i>

9
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:18,500
<i>I'm sorry you lost
a good person in your life.</i>

10
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:22,100
<i>I promise, I won't waste
the life Leon saved.</i>

11
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,000
<i> Thank you.</i>

12
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:26,700
<i>Now, it's time for me
to step up as a mother.</i>

13
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,133
<i> You're going home,</i>

14
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:30,167
and I'll stay with your brother
<i> for now</i>

15
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:32,000
<i> until things get better.</i>

16
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,333
<i> Are we clear?</i>

17
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,333
<i> This place isn't safe.</i>

18
00:00:35,367 --> 00:00:36,533
<i> Then why are you staying?</i>

19
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:37,733
<i> Because this is our home.</i>

20
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:39,700
<i>I'm going to continue
searching for the treasure.</i>

21
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:40,800
<i> Are you serious?</i>

22
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:42,300
<i> We only owe the Arellanos.</i>

23
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:45,400
<i> If you're not an Arellano,
</i>you won't get anything from us.

24
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,000
<i> That's why I need you.</i>

25
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:49,200
<i> Don't you find it strange?</i>

26
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,667
<i>Why is there metal
over there when...</i>

27
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:51,933
<i>that's part of the forest,
right?</i>

28
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:55,367
<i>Just think of this as the
last thing we'll do for them.</i>

29
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:57,067
<i> For our brothers.</i>

30
00:00:57,067 --> 00:00:58,133
<i>- Hey!
- Oh!</i>

31
00:00:58,133 --> 00:00:59,533
<i>- Trixie, run!
- [SCREAMING]</i>

32
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:00,700
[SCREAMING]

33
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:02,367
- [GRUNTS]
- [BLOW LANDS]

34
00:01:06,067 --> 00:01:07,467
Trixie! [PANTING]

35
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:10,267
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:01:10,267 --> 00:01:11,533
Trixie!

37
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:15,133
[PANTING, SQUEALING]

38
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:16,767
Trixie!

39
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:19,133
[CHESKA] Trixie!

40
00:01:19,133 --> 00:01:22,167
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

41
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,133
[PANTING]

42
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:26,633
Where are you, Trixie?

43
00:01:26,633 --> 00:01:29,500
Trixie... Trixie! I can't...

44
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:32,367
[SOBBING]

45
00:01:32,367 --> 00:01:34,033
Help!

46
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:35,633
Kiko!

47
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:37,433
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

48
00:01:37,433 --> 00:01:39,167
Trixie!

49
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:42,133
[WHIMPERING]

50
00:01:42,167 --> 00:01:44,467
[SOBBING]

51
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:45,633
Help!

52
00:01:45,633 --> 00:01:47,567
[SOBBING]

53
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:48,833
[CHESKA] Trixie!

54
00:01:49,867 --> 00:01:51,667
Guys, help! [SOBBING]

55
00:01:51,667 --> 00:01:52,800
Trixie!

56
00:01:53,667 --> 00:01:54,700
Trixie!

57
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,233
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

58
00:01:56,233 --> 00:01:57,500
Help...

59
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:00,667
Bro... Trixie...

60
00:02:01,367 --> 00:02:02,500
Help...

61
00:02:04,133 --> 00:02:05,667
Bro...

62
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,833
[SCREAMING] Help!

63
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,800
Let go of me!

64
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,167
Help!

65
00:02:11,167 --> 00:02:12,533
Trixie!

66
00:02:14,567 --> 00:02:21,500
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:18,833
- [MARTIN] Kiko.
- Mm?

68
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:21,167
Are you okay?

69
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:23,733
What are you doing there?

70
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:25,667
[KIKO] Breathing.

71
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,300
[MARTIN] Lying down?

72
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:30,567
[KIKO] Is that not allowed?

73
00:03:31,667 --> 00:03:33,500
[KIKO] Try it. Come join me.

74
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:39,567
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:41,500
[GIO] I thought something
happened to you.

76
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,333
You were just lying here.

77
00:03:43,567 --> 00:03:45,867
[KIKO] Didn't we
use to do this before?

78
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,667
Hey, Martin, lie down.

79
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:51,900
[GIO] You're not getting him
to lie down.

80
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,367
His clothes will get dirty.

81
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:54,833
- [KIKO CHUCKLES]
- [MARTIN SIGHS]

82
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,467
[MARTIN] Fine.

83
00:03:58,300 --> 00:03:59,400
[MARTIN GRUNTS]

84
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:01,900
[KIKO] Alright!

85
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:04,500
It's exactly like this.

86
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,833
This is what we used to do
before, right?

87
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,367
Back when we were kids?

88
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:11,267
[TONGUE CLICKS, INHALES]

89
00:04:11,633 --> 00:04:13,900
[KIKO] Even for a little while,

90
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:14,967
let's lie down.

91
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:19,300
Breathe.

92
00:04:20,533 --> 00:04:22,667
After everything
we've been through,

93
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:24,767
let's make the most
out of moments like this.

94
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:27,300
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

95
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:29,467
We'll only be able
to breathe easy

96
00:04:29,467 --> 00:04:31,000
once Andy and Sandro
are caught.

97
00:04:33,867 --> 00:04:36,333
I really want all of this
to end.

98
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:37,467
Me too.

99
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:40,800
I want to get back
to running this hotel.

100
00:04:41,933 --> 00:04:44,000
I want this hotel to be
a happy place again,

101
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,333
with all of you here.

102
00:04:46,367 --> 00:04:48,767
So when they come back
and threaten us,

103
00:04:50,267 --> 00:04:51,433
I'll fight them.

104
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:55,233
We'll fight
for a peaceful life.

105
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:58,800
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

106
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,833
For our families' safety.

107
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:04,867
For Dad and the others
to get justice.

108
00:05:07,033 --> 00:05:11,367
So we can finally be free
from the fear in our hearts.

109
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:14,433
[JADE] Once they see you,

110
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:16,667
or once they find out
you're Edward Arellano,

111
00:05:16,667 --> 00:05:18,533
get them talking about Oscalara.

112
00:05:19,033 --> 00:05:20,300
[EDWARD] Okay.

113
00:05:21,667 --> 00:05:23,767
I can take over
questioning them.

114
00:05:23,767 --> 00:05:25,800
What's important is that
we get the map.

115
00:05:30,467 --> 00:05:31,667
Jade, how are you?

116
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,400
I heard about
what happened to Leon.

117
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:36,867
I couldn't come because

118
00:05:36,867 --> 00:05:39,333
I didn't want to add
to your family's worries.

119
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:44,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:05:44,667 --> 00:05:45,700
[SIGHS]

121
00:05:46,867 --> 00:05:48,067
Time is running.

122
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,033
Let's move faster.

123
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:53,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

124
00:05:55,667 --> 00:05:56,867
Tamara.

125
00:05:58,867 --> 00:06:00,800
[TAMARA] You shouldn't have
come back here.

126
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:04,667
You said you only trust
the Arellanos.

127
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:08,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:06:08,533 --> 00:06:09,733
I know you.

129
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:14,633
Can we speak to your
grandmother now?

130
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:20,600
[CREAKS]

131
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:26,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

132
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,067
- [GIO] Kiko.
- Hm?

133
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:33,400
Next time, don't scare us
like that, okay?

134
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:38,000
We really thought you were
going to leave us.

135
00:06:41,133 --> 00:06:42,467
Me?

136
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:43,900
Leave you?

137
00:06:44,567 --> 00:06:46,167
That's not going to happen.

138
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:49,867
Because I won't waste
this life that Leon saved.

139
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:51,767
[KIKO] Promise!

140
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:56,700
- [GIO] What are we doing?
- Let's make a promise.

141
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,900
This is what we always
used to do, right?

142
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,767
You're so corny.

143
00:07:01,767 --> 00:07:03,700
Come on, it's a promise.

144
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:05,433
Like this?

145
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:07,467
- Here.
- Here.

146
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:09,567
Come on. [CHUCKLES]

147
00:07:09,567 --> 00:07:10,600
[KIKO] Martin.

148
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:13,867
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:16,133
- Then what?
- Come on, let's take a selfie!

150
00:07:17,467 --> 00:07:20,067
We already gave in to your
promise thing, and now a selfie?

151
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:22,100
Come on. Moments like this
don't happen often.

152
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:24,167
Come on. We might not get
another chance like this.

153
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:25,733
I don't want to take a picture.

154
00:07:25,733 --> 00:07:27,033
My hair doesn't look good. Tsk.

155
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:28,933
One, two, three.

156
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:31,167
- [CELLPHONE CAMERA SHUTTERS]
- Cheese!

157
00:07:31,167 --> 00:07:32,900
[KIKO] Okay, do a wacky one.

158
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,000
[GIO] A wacky one?

159
00:07:34,467 --> 00:07:36,567
- That was a wacky pose?
- What was that?

160
00:07:36,567 --> 00:07:38,567
- That's good enough.
- I don't think so.

161
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:40,833
- Look.
- Tsk.

162
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:42,633
[MARTIN] You're definitely
the ugliest

163
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:43,800
out of the three of us.

164
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,433
[GIO CHUCKLES]
Look who's talking.

165
00:07:47,033 --> 00:07:53,967
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:08:06,467 --> 00:08:08,200
[AUTOMATED VOICE]<i> The number
</i> you have dialed is either busy

167
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,600
<i> or out of coverage area.</i>

168
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:13,600
Have you seen Trixie?

169
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,767
No, but she and Cheska
were getting ready to go home,

170
00:08:15,767 --> 00:08:16,933
weren't they?

171
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:19,800
They were supposed to,
but Trixie's not in her room.

172
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,833
I'm sure she's here somewhere.

173
00:08:21,867 --> 00:08:23,433
- What about Cheska?
- I don't know either.

174
00:08:23,433 --> 00:08:24,467
- [RAPHIE] Sir.
- Did you find her, Raphie?

175
00:08:24,467 --> 00:08:25,433
I've asked Sari,

176
00:08:25,433 --> 00:08:27,733
but she hasn't seen
Miss Trixie either.

177
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,500
Okay, Gio.

178
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,733
I'll see what I can do.

179
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:37,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:08:37,367 --> 00:08:38,867
Why were you talking to Gio?

181
00:08:38,867 --> 00:08:41,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

182
00:08:41,433 --> 00:08:42,433
No reason.

183
00:08:43,567 --> 00:08:44,867
He was just checking in.

184
00:08:44,867 --> 00:08:45,867
Why?

185
00:08:45,867 --> 00:08:47,900
Did something happen again?

186
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,167
Justin, what happened?

187
00:08:51,733 --> 00:08:52,833
Nothing.

188
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,800
He just wants to know
if you're okay.

189
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:57,933
That's all.

190
00:08:57,933 --> 00:09:04,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:09:08,633 --> 00:09:10,300
[LINE RINGING]

192
00:09:19,867 --> 00:09:22,367
Good afternoon, Grandma.

193
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:24,700
Good day, ma'am.

194
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:28,967
[TAMARA] Grandma hasn't
accepted guests in a long time.

195
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,233
She doesn't leave the house
anymore either.

196
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:35,767
Sir Andy has tried taking her
to the hospital several times,

197
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:37,800
but she always refuses.

198
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:43,033
Grandma,
Sir Andy's son is here.

199
00:09:43,033 --> 00:09:44,900
He wants to talk to you.

200
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:53,467
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

201
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,000
It's nice to meet you, Grandma.

202
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,833
We want to ask you something.

203
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:06,267
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

204
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:07,500
Grandma...

205
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:09,333
Do you know what this is?

206
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:13,967
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

207
00:10:13,967 --> 00:10:16,533
Grandma's vision
has deteriorated.

208
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,033
She won't be able to read it.

209
00:10:26,633 --> 00:10:28,900
"It stands in the flesh,

210
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:31,600
yet never takes a step.

211
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:34,967
Follow the silent path.

212
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:38,000
The secret is
not written on paper,

213
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,300
but hidden on
a surface carved by time.

214
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:44,500
Read the lines as though
they were a sacred oath,

215
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:48,500
for it is there that
the Oscalara draws breath."

216
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:55,433
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

217
00:10:57,367 --> 00:10:59,333
This is her old journal.

218
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:04,000
We don't understand
what is written here.

219
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:10,967
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

220
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:18,467
"ORO VIEJO"

221
00:11:18,467 --> 00:11:21,567
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

222
00:11:21,567 --> 00:11:23,467
<i> "Oro Viejo".</i>

223
00:11:23,467 --> 00:11:25,567
[TAMARA] The lost treasure.

224
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:30,033
Some of the elders on
the island know about it.

225
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:31,833
But...

226
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,900
No one knows if it's true.

227
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,500
What do you mean?

228
00:11:37,467 --> 00:11:39,033
The story goes that

229
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:46,467
a former Governor-General
hid vast amounts of gold here.

230
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:49,433
However, when he died,

231
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:51,967
no one could find Oro Viejo.

232
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,567
<i> Oro Viejo.</i>

233
00:11:54,567 --> 00:11:59,867
[INTRIGUING MUSIC SWELLS]

234
00:12:01,433 --> 00:12:04,167
Sir, I've been trying to
reach Cheska and Trixie.

235
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:05,667
- Okay.
- But no luck.

236
00:12:05,667 --> 00:12:06,500
Thank you, Sari.

237
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,633
- Keep calling them.
- Yes, sir.

238
00:12:08,633 --> 00:12:10,400
That's exactly
what I'm going to do.

239
00:12:11,933 --> 00:12:13,133
Where's Kiko?

240
00:12:13,133 --> 00:12:15,133
In the room
with Aunt Georgia.

241
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:17,900
We won't tell them
until we're sure.

242
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:23,800
Sari, tell Raphie
not to tell anyone yet.

243
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:24,833
Yes, sir.

244
00:12:25,767 --> 00:12:27,467
Nothing still?

245
00:12:28,733 --> 00:12:29,833
Not yet.

246
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,767
But I've checked
most of the cameras.

247
00:12:32,767 --> 00:12:34,800
I don't think
they're here at Hotel 88.

248
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,533
[AUTOMATED VOICE]
<i> ...or out of coverage area.</i>

249
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:39,767
Sir, are you sure
they're not back in Manila?

250
00:12:39,767 --> 00:12:41,067
I called my mom.

251
00:12:41,067 --> 00:12:42,800
She said she hadn't
spoken to Trixie yet,

252
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:46,500
and Trixie usually has someone
pick her up at the port.

253
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,767
Cheska would
let us know before leaving.

254
00:12:51,833 --> 00:12:53,467
[MARTIN EXHALES HEAVILY]

255
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:55,500
They're not with the Almazans.

256
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:57,100
If they're not here or there,

257
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:58,567
then where the hell are they?

258
00:13:00,067 --> 00:13:01,800
[SIGHS]

259
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,900
Grandma...

260
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:06,867
Grandma, what do you know
about Oro Viejo?

261
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:14,733
What are you doing?

262
00:13:14,733 --> 00:13:16,200
Grandma...

263
00:13:16,967 --> 00:13:18,133
Grandma, please.

264
00:13:19,133 --> 00:13:21,033
I'm begging you.

265
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:25,967
We need to find the treasure.

266
00:13:25,967 --> 00:13:29,233
We're not after
the money or the gold.

267
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:33,967
We need to find the treasure
to protect our families

268
00:13:33,967 --> 00:13:36,233
and the people
who are important to us.

269
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:43,167
I lost my father
because of that treasure.

270
00:13:44,567 --> 00:13:47,267
His best friend,
Uncle Mike,

271
00:13:47,267 --> 00:13:48,933
Monette,

272
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,867
and even my brother, Leon.

273
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:56,567
Grandma, please help us.

274
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,833
No one else has to die.

275
00:14:01,933 --> 00:14:06,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

276
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:08,867
Jade, Jade, Jade.

277
00:14:09,667 --> 00:14:11,867
Come on, Jade. Get up.

278
00:14:14,967 --> 00:14:17,267
I'm desperate, Edward.

279
00:14:17,267 --> 00:14:21,100
I need to find it
to end this once and for all.

280
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:26,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,700
[EDWARD SIGHS SHARPLY]

282
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,000
Please.

283
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:32,033
We just need a bit
more time with her.

284
00:14:32,033 --> 00:14:34,800
She might say something
that could help us.

285
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,933
I think you need to go.

286
00:14:38,933 --> 00:14:43,067
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:14:43,067 --> 00:14:46,233
"The secret does not
dwell on paper,

288
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:49,200
but on the back
shaped by time.

289
00:14:50,733 --> 00:14:52,933
Read the markings
as if they were a vow,

290
00:14:54,233 --> 00:14:56,900
for there the
Oscalara breathes."

291
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:58,667
Jade, what are you
talking about?

292
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:01,933
It's behind...

293
00:15:03,233 --> 00:15:05,067
On the back.

294
00:15:05,067 --> 00:15:06,800
It's on her back.

295
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:11,333
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

296
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:14,133
Edward, it's on her back.

297
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:16,200
Can we see it?

298
00:15:19,867 --> 00:15:21,200
Grandma?

299
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,633
Do we show it?

300
00:15:23,633 --> 00:15:30,600
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

301
00:15:38,067 --> 00:15:39,800
The third map.

302
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:46,733
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

303
00:15:47,933 --> 00:15:51,200
Tamara, can I
take a picture of it?

304
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:58,167
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

305
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:00,367
[CAMERA CLICKS]

306
00:16:00,367 --> 00:16:05,233
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

307
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:13,833
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

308
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:22,867
[CHESKA GRUNTING]

309
00:16:24,267 --> 00:16:25,400
[GASPS]

310
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:28,500
Trixie...

311
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,467
Trixie!

312
00:16:29,667 --> 00:16:30,800
Trixie...

313
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,633
Trixie. Trixie!

314
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:34,633
Trixie, wake up.

315
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:36,267
Trixie!

316
00:16:36,267 --> 00:16:37,600
Trixie, are you all right?

317
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:40,400
Trixie, Trixie...

318
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,533
Trixie...

319
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:44,233
Trixie... Trixie...

320
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,600
Trixie, are you all right?

321
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:48,433
- Trixie...
- Mhm...

322
00:16:48,433 --> 00:16:51,900
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

323
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:53,433
[CHESKA] Trixie?

324
00:16:53,433 --> 00:16:54,800
Trixie, are you all right?

325
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,700
Trixie...

326
00:16:58,267 --> 00:16:59,400
[CHESKA INHALES SHARPLY]

327
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,200
[TRIXIE GRUNTS]

328
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,833
[BED CREAKS]

329
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:08,267
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

330
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:10,267
How did we get here?

331
00:17:10,267 --> 00:17:11,567
I don't know.

332
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:13,333
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

333
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:15,167
Cheska, were we kidnapped?

334
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,567
Where are we?

335
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:19,700
How did we get here?

336
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:21,667
I don't know. It's that man.

337
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:24,367
That man brought us here.

338
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:25,433
What man?

339
00:17:25,433 --> 00:17:27,600
- Which man?
- [CREAKS]

340
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:29,367
- Cheska!
- Shh!

341
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:31,500
Cheska, what are we going to do?

342
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:32,767
[WHIMPERING]

343
00:17:32,767 --> 00:17:34,767
We'll get out of here.

344
00:17:34,767 --> 00:17:37,333
I'll go to Sir Henri myself
and make a report.

345
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,433
I don't care if less than
24 hours have passed.

346
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:41,867
Cheska and Trixie won't
go missing for no reason!

347
00:17:43,433 --> 00:17:44,533
Cheska?

348
00:17:46,567 --> 00:17:47,967
She's missing?

349
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:54,967
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

350
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:56,667
[GIO] Auntie...

351
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,567
Kiko...

352
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:01,700
We've been trying to contact
Cheska and Trixie.

353
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:03,433
But neither of them
answered our calls.

354
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:04,833
What?

355
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:08,367
[GEORGIA BREATHES SHAKILY]

356
00:18:08,367 --> 00:18:10,000
Are they missing?

357
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,000
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

358
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,800
Are they missing?!

359
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,633
Yes.

360
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,867
[GEORGIA GASPS]

361
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,333
[CHESKA] Just wait.

362
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:24,733
It's so tight, Trixie.

363
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:27,867
Chloe, you're only
making the knot tighter.

364
00:18:27,867 --> 00:18:29,433
Hurry up.

365
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:31,733
Wait a minute, don't move.

366
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:36,533
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

367
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:40,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

368
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:43,233
- [SCREAMS]
- Trixie!

369
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:44,533
Trixie...

370
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:47,600
Hey, hey, hey!
What will you do to us?

371
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:49,767
What are you going
to do with us? Let us go!

372
00:18:49,767 --> 00:18:51,433
Let us go! Have mercy on us!

373
00:18:51,433 --> 00:18:52,767
Let us go!

374
00:18:52,767 --> 00:18:53,900
[CHESKA EXCLAIMS]

375
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:56,833
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

376
00:18:56,867 --> 00:19:01,033
[SQUEALING]

377
00:19:01,033 --> 00:19:03,633
[CHESKA] Trixie! Trixie!

378
00:19:03,633 --> 00:19:05,033
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

379
00:19:05,033 --> 00:19:06,367
[PHONE BEEPS]

380
00:19:06,367 --> 00:19:10,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

381
00:19:10,767 --> 00:19:13,267
- Cheska, are you hurt?
- Trixie.

382
00:19:17,533 --> 00:19:19,333
[CHESKA] What are you
going to do?

383
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:20,833
Trixie, is that your phone?

384
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:21,833
Yes.

385
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:23,400
It's my phone.

386
00:19:25,767 --> 00:19:27,933
I'll file a report to
Sir Henri right now.

387
00:19:27,933 --> 00:19:29,233
They already know
that Sandro is alive,

388
00:19:29,267 --> 00:19:31,967
and with the amount of deaths
here, I know they'll help us.

389
00:19:31,967 --> 00:19:33,933
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

390
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:36,800
[PHONE RINGING]

391
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,400
- It's Trixie!
- Ma.

392
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:39,933
Trixie! Where are you
and Cheska?

393
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:41,800
We've all been trying
to call you!

394
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:42,767
Cheska?

395
00:19:42,767 --> 00:19:44,767
- Cheska, dear!
- Cheska.

396
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:48,467
- [CHESKA]<i> Mama...
</i>- [TRIXIE CRYING]

397
00:19:48,467 --> 00:19:50,767
[WHIMPERING]

398
00:19:50,767 --> 00:19:52,600
- [TRIXIE]<i> Brother...
</i>- [CHESKA PUFFING]

399
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,433
<i> First of all...</i>

400
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:58,067
<i> Don't tell the police
about this.</i>

401
00:19:59,533 --> 00:20:02,367
<i> If you don't want us to die.</i>

402
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,967
[CRYING CONTINUES]

403
00:20:03,967 --> 00:20:05,033
- What?
- Where--

404
00:20:05,033 --> 00:20:06,567
- What are you talking about?!
- Where are they?

405
00:20:06,567 --> 00:20:07,967
[CHESKA] All of the...

406
00:20:07,967 --> 00:20:10,567
<i> All of the clues</i>

407
00:20:10,567 --> 00:20:13,400
<i> in finding the treasure...</i>

408
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,767
<i> shall be given to him.</i>

409
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,800
<i> To him? Who is he?</i>

410
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:18,933
<i> Who abducted you?</i>

411
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:20,800
<i> Where are you?</i>

412
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:22,933
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

413
00:20:22,933 --> 00:20:24,100
[CHESKA] This...

414
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:27,667
This is the price
for both of our lives.

415
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:30,067
- [MARTIN]<i> What?
</i>- [KIKO] Cheska, where are you?!

416
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:31,533
[GEORGIA] Dear!

417
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:32,700
[CRYING]

418
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:35,067
<i>If you don't abide
by this deal...</i>

419
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,967
<i> both of us will die.</i>

420
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:42,400
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

421
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,400
- Trixie!
- Cheska!

422
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,400
Cheska!

423
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,800
Kiko!

424
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:48,400
Who kidnapped your sister?!

425
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:52,367
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

426
00:20:52,867 --> 00:20:56,033
[CRYING]

427
00:20:56,033 --> 00:20:57,867
[BLADE SWISHES]

428
00:20:57,867 --> 00:21:03,067
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

429
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:07,333
[EDWARD] Tamara,
thank you for your help.

430
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:12,367
We know it's not easy for your
grandmother to talk to people.

431
00:21:13,067 --> 00:21:14,300
Thank you.

432
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,633
I hope Grandma's not mistaken
in trusting you

433
00:21:18,633 --> 00:21:20,433
and showing you the map she has.

434
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,600
This for our families' lives.

435
00:21:26,467 --> 00:21:28,233
Thank you very much.

436
00:21:28,233 --> 00:21:35,200
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

437
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:50,967
Are you heading home?

438
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:54,467
I'm going to the hotel.

439
00:21:54,467 --> 00:21:57,033
I'll just show this map to Kiko.

440
00:21:59,567 --> 00:22:01,167
Would you like me
to drive you there?

441
00:22:01,167 --> 00:22:02,267
No thanks. I'll be fine.

442
00:22:04,633 --> 00:22:06,600
Thank you for helping me.

443
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:09,467
I can go home alone.

444
00:22:09,467 --> 00:22:12,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

445
00:22:12,467 --> 00:22:13,600
Jade.

446
00:22:17,667 --> 00:22:19,233
Sorry for your loss.

447
00:22:21,267 --> 00:22:24,367
I know how much
Leon means to you.

448
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:34,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

449
00:22:37,467 --> 00:22:38,633
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

450
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:39,967
[CHESKA] Trixie...

451
00:22:40,633 --> 00:22:42,467
Trixie, Trixie, Trixie...

452
00:22:42,467 --> 00:22:44,300
Trixie, take a breath.

453
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:46,300
- Trixie, Trixie, Trixie...
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

454
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:48,700
Trixie, listen to me.
Breathe, breathe.

455
00:22:48,733 --> 00:22:50,067
Breathe, calm down.

456
00:22:50,067 --> 00:22:52,100
- Brother, where are you?
- Calm down, he heard you.

457
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:54,267
Martin heard you.

458
00:22:54,267 --> 00:22:55,433
He will help us.

459
00:22:55,433 --> 00:22:57,267
Trixie, calm down.

460
00:22:57,267 --> 00:22:59,267
Trixie, calm down. Calm down.

461
00:22:59,267 --> 00:23:01,400
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WHIMPERING]

462
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:03,400
- Follow me. Come on, inhale!
- [INHALES DEEPLY]

463
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,400
Inhale, inhale!

464
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:08,400
- Exhale, exhale.
- [EXHALES DEEPLY]

465
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,633
- Inhale. Exhale.
- [BREATHING DEEPLY]

466
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:12,500
Calm down, calm down.

467
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:14,500
- Cheska, I don't want to die.
- No, no.

468
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:16,633
[SOBBING]

469
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:21,233
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

470
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:24,200
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

471
00:23:32,667 --> 00:23:35,633
[SANDRO] Just one mistake

472
00:23:36,267 --> 00:23:38,667
from your brothers...

473
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:43,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

474
00:23:43,267 --> 00:23:46,233
And you'll both explode.

475
00:23:48,667 --> 00:23:50,633
You're a demon!

476
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:52,000
[CRYING]

477
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:54,367
You're an animal! You bastard!

478
00:23:56,267 --> 00:23:58,133
[CHESKA] You are an animal!

479
00:23:58,133 --> 00:23:59,133
[TRIXIE] No!

480
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:00,667
No, wait!

481
00:24:00,667 --> 00:24:02,667
Wait!

482
00:24:02,667 --> 00:24:10,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

483
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:17,167
<i>Please, just give it to me!
I need the map!</i>

484
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:19,033
<i> Just give it! Give it.</i>

485
00:24:19,033 --> 00:24:20,133
<i> Luna!</i>

486
00:24:20,433 --> 00:24:22,567
<i> We will not give this to him.</i>

487
00:24:22,567 --> 00:24:25,400
Our sisters' lives depend on it!

488
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:26,567
<i> But, you!</i>

489
00:24:26,567 --> 00:24:28,167
<i>You've got money on
your mind again, don't you?!</i>

490
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,367
<i> That's enough!</i>

491
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:30,400
<i> Is that how you really see me?</i>

492
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,767
<i>Do I look like I only care
about the money?</i>

493
00:24:31,767 --> 00:24:33,600
<i>- Isn't it true?
- You bastard!</i>

494
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:36,267
<i>Gio, what brings you here?
Do you need anything?</i>

495
00:24:36,267 --> 00:24:37,367
<i> There's a problem, sir.</i>

496
00:24:37,367 --> 00:24:40,233
<i>I'll send you the pictures
of the map we got.</i>

497
00:24:40,667 --> 00:24:42,267
<i> I changed my mind.</i>

498
00:24:42,267 --> 00:24:46,067
<i>Give me the treasure
within one day!</i>

499
00:24:47,267 --> 00:24:49,433
<i> Help!</i>

500
00:24:49,433 --> 00:24:50,600
<i> We'll bring her home.</i>

501
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,433
<i> Do you understand me, Kiko?</i>

502
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:55,267
<i> Cheska... Trixie...</i>

503
00:24:55,267 --> 00:24:57,400
<i>None of our siblings
will die anymore.</i>
